pr_body:
Changes trackable behavior of `login_user` when IP can not be detected
from a request from 'untrackable' to `None` value.  (closes #448)

Signed-off-by: Jiri Kuncar <jiri.kuncar@cern.ch>

I ran into this when configuring EasyBuild with a custom log format (`--log-format='easybuild,eb-%(name)s.log'`) and then using `--job`, which uses `generate_cmd_line` to dump the full configuration as a list of command line options, which uses `shell_quote` internally.

Without this, the value passed to `--log-format` is included unquoted (`--log-format=easybuild,eb-%(name)s.log`) in the job command line, which then fails with `syntax error near unexpected token `('`.

@stdweird: please review

The actual output in the README example is as follow
```
{
    "Id": "S3-Account-Permissions", 
    "Statement": [
        {
            "Action": [
                "s3:*"
            ], 
            "Effect": "Allow", 
            "Principal": {
                "AWS": [
                    "arn:aws:iam:user/Bob::123456789012"
                ]
            }, 
            "Resource": [
                "arn:aws:s3:::my_corporate_bucket/*"
            ], 
            "Sid": "1"
        }
    ], 
    "Version": "2012-10-17"
}
```

Minor doc change for consistency.

Making sure we're targeting the right things here. I've mostly been testing by running desktop and making sure things look "right". I wish we had a better way to measure this stuff -- I suppose it means I need to do a better job reviewing these 😅 .

Behavior to know about with styled-jsx:

```jsx
<ul>
  {props.children}
</ul>
<style jsx>{`
  :global(li) {
    background-color: DeepPink;
  }
`}</style>
```

Will target _all_ `li` because there's no selector preceding it whereas:

```jsx
<ul>
  {props.children}
</ul>
<style jsx>{`
  ul :global(li) {
    background-color: DeepPink;
  }
`}</style>
```

will create `ul` with a className like `jsx-2352357` and the css becomes:

```css
ul.jsx-2352357 li {
    background-color: DeepPink;
}
```

[Further background on how styled-jsx works](https://github.com/zeit/styled-jsx/tree/v2#how-it-works)

- better variable name
- add term character setting;
- replace version function with dummy

